title: High school update Friday's multi-sport results, highlights |
text:
FIELD HOCKEY Lakeland 3, Smithfield 2, OT
G–L, Waterfield, Munford, Leonard; S, Hedgepeth, Lange.
Shannon Leonards goal with 8:54 left in overtime, propelled Lakeland to victory.
Private schools
Norfolk Collegiate 4, St. Margaret’s 0
G—NC, White 2, Wentworth, Zooss.
Logan White scored two goals for the Oaks.
BOYS SOCCER
Private schools
Norfolk Christian 5, Portsmouth Christian 4
G—NC, Daffron 2, Clark, Caravas, Sisco; PC, Harrison 3, Hollis
Clayton Daffron scored the winning goal with 1:30 remaining in the 2nd half.
St. Christopher’s 4, Norfolk Academy 1
G—SC, O’Neal 2, Reinhardt, Vaeth; NA; Schneider.
Beach Breakers 10, Summit Christian 0
G—BB, D.Heard, Gilley, Effler 4, Penick, Rawlings, Welsh, Dunton.
GIRLS VOLLEYBALL
#8 StoneBridge d. Denbigh Baptist, 3-0
(25-17, 25-19, 25-18)
Allie Plumlee had 20 kills. Aradhana Khubani had 35 assists.
Private schools
Oaktree d. Beach Breakers, 3-1
(25-15, 23-25, 25-16, 26-24)
Jessica Bissmeyer had 19 kills and 2 aces. Jamie Bissmeyer had 30 assists, 4 aces and 5 kills.
